Police in Malindi have arrested at least 70 revelers at Dhome Bar and Restaurant for flouting Covid-19 protocols. However, some traders have accused police of selectively targeting restaurants in the implementation of Covide-19 guidelines amid the partial reopening of the joints across the country. Ms Ruth George, resident and trader blames that police for raiding Dhome Bar and Restaurant at 4pm Thursday. Â  She blamed the police for taking advantage of the Covid-19 guidelines to harass business people in the area. Malindi Sub-County police boss Joe Lekuta said he was not aware of the arrests. He accused bars and restaurants of flouting the Covid-19 guidelines.